            <title>[MAHOUT-645] Elkan distance optimization for VectorBenchmarks class</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-645</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Implementation of first lemma of Elkan&apos;s optimization:&lt;br/&gt;
Given three points x, b, c (where b and c are centroids):&lt;br/&gt;
                                           d(b,c)&amp;gt;=2d(x.b) then d(x,c)&amp;gt;=d(x,b)&lt;br/&gt;
in which case we wouldn&apos;t need to calculate d(x,c). This is used to find the closest centroid for every point x.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Ubuntu Linux at Intel Core2 Duo P7450 @ 2.13GHz&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
